name: narrative-report-missisquoi-national-wildlife-refuge-september-october-november-and-decemb-305ed
notes: This narrative report for Missisquoi NWR outlines Refuge accomplishments from September through December of 1951. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, predators, rodents, mammals, raptors, and fish- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments and plantings. Resource management is outlined; topics include grazing, haying, and fur harvesting. A progress report on field investigations and applied research is also provided. The public relations section of the report describes recreational uses, Refuge visitors, hunting, fishing, and violations. N-R forms and photographs are attached.
